<br>
For a ranger to get this level of archery damage the following is required:<br>
1. 59 AA points  (EQ + AM3 + CF3).  Don't forget that this is HARD for rangers to get, as we are not the &quot;favored&quot; class for participating in AE groups, we can't quad-kite, so we have to grind them out one-by-one.  I play a lot and still only have less than a third of the required AA points.<br>
2. The best bow in the game.  Again, I belong to a strong guild, but as luck has it, I still don't have a primal bow, or the bow that drops off the AoW.  95% of level 60 rangers will never have a better bow than a bow from DN. With an &quot;average&quot; (but good) DN bow, a warder's archery damage is cut by 30 % from the peak levels you read about.<br>
3. The best arrows in the game.  This requires a lot of questing and getting your fletching skill above 202.  <br>
4. Trueshot discipline.  Recycle time = 74 minutes.  Normal archery has about 1/3 the damage of Trueshot discipline.<br>
5. Target is not moving / snared / rooted.  If the target MOB so much as twitches, our archery damage is cut by 50%.  If a wizard/shaman/druid/paladin roots the MOB (and they do this a lot for some damn reason), our archery damage is cut by 50%.<br>
6. Target is not touching a wall.  If the target MOB so much as puts its toe into the wall, our archery damage is cut by 100%  (i.e. ZERO damage).  And then we have to wait 74 minutes for our discipline to recycle, all because someone pushed the MOB wrong, or a caster ping ponged it next to a wall.<br>
7. No one steps in front of you.  Archery is Line-of-Sight.  If a person obscures your LoS, your archery damage is cut by 100% (i.e. ZERO).  In a typical raid condition, with 30 people jostling in front of a MOB, often 25-50% of archery shots are absorbed by players in my LoS.  Worst offenders for obscuring LoS are levitated casters/healers.<br>
<br>
Now that I put this into perspective, let me tell you what a warder typically gets while using his Trueshot discipline in a typical raid:<br>
* With Trueshot + 30/38 bow fleeting quiver + shissar haste + 3-damage arrows my dps is slightly LESS than melee.<br>
* I expect to have, after 59 AA points, once evey 74 minutes using my Trueshot discipline, about 2x the damage of melee (unless I get lucky and get a uber-bow, where it may change to 2.5x to 3x), given the data I have seen from parseing tests.  This is still less damage than a rogue will do.<br>
 <p>Locz Agneyastra <BR>
